<p>Timing your visit to <strong>Little Boracay in Calatagan, Batangas</strong> correctly makes a significant difference to your experience. Here's everything you need to know about the best time to visit — by season, month, and time of day.</p>

<h2>Best Season: November to May (Dry Season)</h2>
<p>The <strong>dry season from November to May</strong> is the best time to visit Little Boracay. During these months you can expect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Clear skies and sunny weather</li>
  <li>Calm seas and reliable boat operations</li>
  <li>Best water visibility for swimming and snorkeling</li>
  <li>Lower risk of rain or typhoon disruption</li>
</ul>
<p>Peak season within the dry season is <strong>December through April</strong> — expect higher visitor numbers on weekends. Book floating cottages well in advance during these months.</p>

<h2>Typhoon Season: June to October</h2>
<p>The wet season runs from June to October, coinciding with the Philippine typhoon season. During this period:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Higher chance of rain and rough seas</li>
  <li>Boat operations may be suspended on bad weather days</li>
  <li>Some weekends may still be viable — always check weather forecasts</li>
</ul>
<p>Always check <strong>PAGASA</strong> (Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration) and confirm with local operators before travelling during typhoon season.</p>

<h2>Best Time of Day: Morning</h2>
<p><strong>Morning is the best time of day</strong> to visit Little Boracay. Aim to arrive at the jump-off point by <strong>7–9 AM</strong> for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Low tide conditions — widest sandbar, shallowest water</li>
  <li>Cooler temperatures before peak afternoon heat</li>
  <li>Calmer sea conditions</li>
  <li>Best light for photography</li>
  <li>First access to floating cottages</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best Day of the Week: Weekdays</h2>
<p>If your schedule allows, <strong>weekday visits</strong> (Monday–Friday) offer a quieter, less crowded experience. Weekends — especially Saturdays — are the busiest. If you must go on a weekend, arrive early and book ahead.</p>

